As most of us stare stage six power cuts in the face this evening, Cape Town is able to keep its customers on Stage 4. Cape Town mayor Geordin Hill-Lewis discussed this with eNCA's Sally Burdett. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The rest of South Africa will continue to experience Stage 6 blackouts on Wednesday. Meanwhile, those in Cape Town will only go up to Stage 4. READ: SA’s electricity crisis | Hopes to get back to Stage 2 soon The City is using the Steenbras hydroelectric plant to mitigate the impact. Watch the video above for more details on this story.